## 4. Current implementation

- **AuditEvent schema:** Platform DB; event_type (business | security | technical | metrics), level, module, action, entity_type, entity_id, user_id, tenant_id, description, meta (JSON), correlation_id, request_id, etc.
- **AuditService:** getAuditService(prisma); logSecurityEvent (sync, fail-safe); logBusinessEvent, logTechnicalEvent, logMetricsEvent (async via queue). Queue writes to AuditQueue; worker processes and calls logAuditEvent.
- **logAuditEvent:** Direct insert into AuditEvent (used by security path and by worker).
- **AuditWorker:** Processes AuditQueue, calls logAuditEvent; started by backend with platformPrisma.
- **auditMiddleware:** Captures request metadata; can log CUD operations (integration with routes). Module never "unknown" — falls back to `"api"`. Reads `req.audit.module` (explicit from routes) and `req.auditUserDisplay` (user_name, user_email) for display.
- **auditHelpers:** auditCreate, auditUpdate, auditDelete, auditSecurity (re-exported); **auditCreateWithSkip, auditUpdateWithSkip, auditDeleteWithSkip** for route handlers that log an explicit event (set `req.audit.skipAudit = true` to avoid duplicate middleware event).
- **Person display:** Backend personDisplayMiddleware caches Person display_name/email by (user_id, tenant_id); populates `req.auditUserDisplay`. Call **invalidatePersonDisplayCache(userId, tenantId)** when Person is updated/deleted. Frontend can pass **userDisplayName** and **userEmail** via setAuthToken options so API requests send x-user-name and x-user-email as fallback.

