## 4.1. Implemented events

Audit events come from three sources. Stored fields include **user_id** and **user_name** (person display name) for human context; **description** should be human-readable where possible; **meta** holds system info (method, path, request/response, before/after).

| Source | Description | Module / entity_type | Notes |
|--------|-------------|---------------------|--------|
| **Middleware (CUD requests)** | `METHOD path` (e.g. `POST /api/work-items`) or improved when path is empty | From path: `api/<segment>` → module; entity from path segment | Unknown POST (e.g. `POST /`) improved with body keys or "POST (no path)" so events are traceable. |
| **Explicit app routes** | Human-readable (e.g. "Created work item WBS-001 (Phase 1)", "Updated project CRM Implementation (PRJ-001)") | Set per route (work_items, projects, timesheets, etc.) | auditCreate, auditUpdate, auditDelete called after CUD with description and entity_type. |
| **Platform / tenant** | Security and platform admin actions | security, tenants, users, etc. | logSecurityEvent or platform routes. |

**App-domain examples (explicit events):**

- **work_items:** Created/Updated/Deleted work item with key and name; meta includes key, name, project_id; update includes before/after.
- **projects:** Updated project with code and name (e.g. "Updated project CRM Implementation (PRJ-001)").
- **timesheets / time_entries:** Create, update, delete with human-readable description and entity id.
- **people, contacts, opportunities, proposals, sales:** Create, update, delete with descriptive text and entity_type (person, contact, opportunity, proposal, sale).
- **workflows:** Step create/update/delete; workflow transitions (e.g. allowed transitions, submit).

**Improving usefulness:**

- Store both **user_id** and **user_name** (person display name) so logs show who acted without lookups.
- Prefer **human-readable description** for explicit events; **meta.request.method/path** (and meta.requestBody) provide system-meaningful detail.
- For middleware-only events (no explicit audit call), description is method + path; when path is missing or "/", use "POST (no path)" and derive module from body when possible to reduce "unknown" entries.
- **Detail panel:** When an audit event is selected in the UI, the platform’s standard detail panel shows all associated fields (including meta, correlation_id, request_id, before/after) in a readable layout.
- **Activity tab:** Detail panels use a subset of audit events (CRUD for that entity) to populate the Activity tab. The list API supports **entity_type** and **entity_id** filters. Display format is human-readable (e.g. "01/12/2026 Matt Rankin created Lead", "01/12/2026 Matt Rankin updated Lead (Phone number)"). Update detail can come from meta.changedFields or from the event description.
- **Cache invalidation API:** Backend exposes **GET /api/cache-events** (Server-Sent Events) with auth (Bearer or `?token=`). Frontend webhookHandler subscribes via EventSource (or WebSocket when enabled) to receive cache invalidation events and refresh permissions/roles/users/app caches. Person cache invalidation is triggered on Person CUD so audit display stays correct.

